
Overview of verb suggest

The verb suggest has 5 senses (first 5 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (57) propose, suggest, advise -- (make a proposal, declare a plan for something; "the senator proposed to abolish the sales tax")
2. (21) hint, suggest -- (drop a hint; intimate by a hint)
3. (19) suggest, intimate -- (imply as a possibility; "The evidence suggests a need for more clarification")
4. (14) indicate, suggest -- (suggest the necessity of an intervention; in medicine; "Tetracycline is indicated in such cases")
5. (12) suggest, evoke, paint a picture -- (call to mind; "this remark evoked sadness")
